this file will help you configure the associated handler
into the Spout Plugin named "MoreMaterials" (v1.8)

This file tell how to use the handler 
		----- FireBallItemHandler v1.1 -----
originally programmed by Cybermaxke and updated by Stan_Fear

 > what is it meant to do ?

allow the player interacting with the bloc or the item to launch a FireBball
 
 > How to use ?
 
0/ download the handler
 
1/ put the handler in your handler folder (serveurRoot/plugins/MoreMaterials/Handlers/)

2/ If you are Not a SMP developer :
	put all your SMP into the materials folder 
	(serveurRoot/plugins/MoreMaterials/Materials/)
		You're done !

   If you are a SMP developer : 
    add and modify the following into your Yaml (<text> are meant to be replaced):
    
Handlers:
__<event>: #name of the event that will trigger the handler
____- Name: "FireBallItemHandler"
______power: <power of the explosion> # The power of the explosion when the fireball touch a block
                                      # must be float, where 4F is the TNT power
______setOnFire:<true|false> # whether the explosion must set nearby block into fire 
                             # (should be set to true for a napalm bomb)
______velocity:<speed> # the speed of the fireball 
                       # must be float




